  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/943",
  "title": "urlSync.threshold seems not to work",
  "body": "According to the [docs](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/#initialization)\n\n![unbenannt](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/36167/13926061/f35e5826-ef8a-11e5-80ca-60f97fb2f599.PNG)\n\n`urlSync.threshold` should update the URL but delayed by700 ms. This seems not to work for me, it even seems to block typing into the search box while the URL is beeing updated. (Can not be proven.)\n\nSo it works, the URL is updated, but it definitely does not delay the URL update by 1000 ms. \n\n```\nvar search = instantsearch({\n    appId:      '...',\n    apiKey:     '...',\n    indexName:  '...',\n    urlSync:    {\n        useHash:    true,\n        threshold:  1000 // This seems not to work\n    },\n    searchFunction: function (helper) {\n        helper.search();\n    },\n    searchParameters: {\n        typoTolerance: true,\n    },\n});\n\nsearch.addWidget(\n    instantsearch.widgets.searchBox({\n        container:      '#q',\n        autofocus:      true,\n        wrapInput:      false,\n        queryHook:      $.throttle(function(query, search) {\n            if ($.trim(query).length == 0) {\n                return false;\n            } else { /* set empty result list */ }\n            search(query);\n        }, 1000),\n    })\n);\n```\n\nOr is this only about the browser history?\n",
